    19 def translate_error({msg, opts}) do
    20 # When using gettext, we typically pass the strings we want
    21 # to translate as a static argument:
    22 #
    23 # # Translate "is invalid" in the "errors" domain
    24 # dgettext "errors", "is invalid"
    25 #
    26 # # Translate the number of files with plural rules
    27 # dngettext "errors", "1 file", "%{count} files", count

    30 # are defined inside Ecto, we need to translate them dynamically.
    31 # This requires us to call the Gettext module passing our gettext
    32 # backend as first argument.
    33 #
    34 # Note we use the "errors" domain, which means translations
    35 # should be written to the errors.po file. The :count option is
    36 # set by Ecto and indicates we should also apply plural rules.
    37 2 if count = opts[:count] do
    38 0 Gettext.dngettext(ParkappWeb.Gettext, "errors", msg, msg, count, opts)
    39 else
    40 2 Gettext.dgettext(ParkappWeb.Gettext, "errors", msg, opts)
